Adding header support.

Issue #11 describes and exemplify the reason why ```kthresher``` is only removing headers of installed kernel images. There will be cases where headers may lie down whenever there is no kernel images for them.
Fix typo introduced in previous commit when searching for a list of installed kernel images.

Adding support for "old"i virtual kernel packages.

Virtual kernel packages were intented to be used for virtual instances but later deprecated in favor of linux-image-generic as outlined in https://help.ubuntu.com/community/ServerFaq#What_are_the_differences_between_the_server_and_virtual_kernels.3F.

Adding cron.daily under docs.

Will help to Fix #5, expecting the package will use these to have a cronjob as well as the configuration in docs/kthresher.conf.example to define what actions to perform.
